text: C64 or C-64 may refer to : * Commodore 64, one of the most successful home computers of the 1980s * C-64 (Michigan county highway), a road in the United States * C-64 Norseman, an aircraft * C64 (field gun), a late 19th-century field gun by Krupp * Ruy Lopez, chess opening numbered C64 in the Encyclopedia of Chess Openings * Renal cell carcinoma, coded as C64 in the International Classification of Diseases 10th edition * Commodore 64 (band), a Hip-hop group * Caldwell 64 (NGC 2362), an open cluster in the constellation Canis Major
title: C64
